        "timestamp": "2018-05-17 10:42:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> > could you put all the changes regarding to removing of memcached\n > > from ocata into a single patch? e.g. the changes on run.sh.\n > thanks\n > \n > Maybe it's my lack of knowledge about the Docker image building\n > process. Is this happen after a change has merged? or there is a\n > cron job which runs every specific hour or day? I did this under\n > the assumption that the process is on demand.\n\nBy default it is a daily jjb to build the docker image. You can trigger the jjb to build docker image immediately by reply \"please release\"",
